UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 1578
1 AN ACT relating to health services.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 Section 1. KRS 205.010 is amended to read as follows:
4 As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
5 (1) "Cabinet" means the Cabinet for Health and Family Services;
6 (2) "Secretary" means the secretary for health and family services or his or her
7 authorized representative;
8 (3) "Public assistance" means money grants, assistance in kind, or services to or for the
9 benefit of needy aged, needy blind, needy permanently and totally disabled persons,
10 needy children, or persons with whom a needy child lives or a family containing a
11 combination of these categories, except that the term shall not be construed to
12 permit the granting of financial aid where the purpose of such aid is to obtain an
13 abortion. For purposes of this section and KRS 205.560, "abortion" means an act,
14 procedure, device, or prescription administered or prescribed for a pregnant woman
15 by any person, including the pregnant woman herself, producing premature
16 expulsion of the fetus. Abortion does not include an induced premature birth
17 intended to produce a live viable child;
18 (4) "Needy child" means a child who has been deprived of parental support by reasons
19 prescribed by regulations within the scope of Title IV of the Social Security Act, its
20 amendments, and federal regulations and who does not have otherwise provided for
21 him or her a subsistence compatible with decency and health;
22 (5) "Parent," in addition to biological or adoptive parent, shall include stepparent;
23 (6) "Needy aged" means a person who has attained the age of sixty-five (65) and who
24 is unable to provide for himself or herself and who does not have otherwise
25 provided for him or her a subsistence compatible with decency and health;
26 (7) "Needy blind" means a person who has no vision or whose vision is so defective as
27 to prevent the performance of ordinary activities for which eyesight is essential and
